<BaseLayout
  title="Best Time to Visit Korea: Season-by-Season Guide"
  description="When to visit Korea: spring cherry blossoms, summer heat and festivals, autumn foliage, and winter. What each season is like for travelers."
>
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Essentials</p>
      <h1>Best Time to Visit Korea</h1>
      <p>What each season is like — so you can pick yours.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <article class="article wrap">
    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Quick answer</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Spring (April–May)</strong> and <strong>autumn
        (late September–November)</strong> are the most popular seasons — mild
        weather, cherry blossoms in spring, and colorful foliage in autumn.
        Summer is hot, humid, and lively with festivals; winter is cold, crisp,
        and good for snow and quieter sightseeing.
      </p>

      <div class="fact-box">
        <h4>Season at a glance</h4>
        <div class="fact-grid">
          <div class="fact"><span class="k">Spring</span><span class="v">Mild · cherry blossoms · busy</span></div>
          <div class="fact"><span class="k">Summer</span><span class="v">Hot &amp; humid · festivals · rainy spell</span></div>
          <div class="fact"><span class="k">Autumn</span><span class="v">Crisp · foliage · great for hiking</span></div>
          <div class="fact"><span class="k">Winter</span><span class="v">Cold · snow · quieter, cheaper</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Spring</h2>
      <p>
        Cherry blossoms sweep from the south up to Seoul over a few weeks. It's a
        beautiful but popular time, so book accommodation early. Days are mild;
        pack layers for cool mornings and evenings.
      </p>

      <h2>Summer</h2>
      <p>
        Expect heat and humidity, plus a rainy spell in mid-summer. It's festival
        season — beaches, music, and night markets are at their liveliest. Stay
        hydrated and plan indoor breaks during the hottest hours.
      </p>

      <h2>Autumn</h2>
      <p>
        Many travelers' favorite: clear skies, comfortable temperatures, and
        striking autumn foliage in the mountains and palaces. Ideal for hiking
        and long days of sightseeing.
      </p>

      <h2>Winter</h2>
      <p>
        Cold and dry, with snow in much of the country — good for ski resorts and
        atmospheric, less-crowded sightseeing. Dress warmly in layers.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="disclosure">
      Seasonal patterns are general and vary year to year; check current
      forecasts and festival dates before you plan around a specific event.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
